I’m blessed and fortunate to have been mothered, mentored, big sistered, and befriended by so many amazing women throughout my life. 
When I look at my son, one of the most incredible things I see is how much he’s learned, that he didn’t learn from me. Most of which has been amazing. What I’ve learned from this, is that it truly takes a Village. 
I’m grateful to all who have had even the smallest part in helping to shape me in becoming the woman I am today. I don’t have photos of them all, but they are loved nonetheless.. 
Here’s to lending a hand, an ear, a shoulder, or a word when and where it’s needed. Mothering happens in so many ways, shapes, forms and sizes.
• 
Here’s to the Village.. Happy Mothers Day to all.❤️
The QUEEN of everything.. All hail the Queen.. Heart💔 I’m goin to bed.. Rest well Queen..

At this point it feels like Covid was a time ago, that things are mostly back to normal, and that we are past what most of us would like to put behind us, and never think about again. 
•
I know I certainly would…
It was one of the biggest events in the lives of every person on earth, yet I don’t think many comprehend the added impact to creatives. This is particularly true, for musicians. I wondered every day would things ever be normal enough again to travel and perform my own music? To be face to face with the listener?
•
These are my first travel dates since 2018 and I am beyond thrilled to be able to connect with you again. What we have missed cannot properly be put into words..
I have missed the connection of music more than I can say. I can’t wait to see you.
•
Get your tickets in advance. Links in bio. See you at a show!❤️

It’s all happening & I can’t even express how thrilled I am! So many of you have already been emailing, texting, & DM’ing that you’re coming to a show!! 
Let me give a brief run down of what’s coming up..
•
First up, 4 Shows/2 nights [Fri 11.10 & 
Sat 11.11] at Good Times Jazz in Savannah, Ga @goodtimesjazz. I’ll be making my debut here & everything I’ve ever heard about Good Times has been stellar, so really excited to perform at this legendary venue.. The band is @lawrencebuckner on Bass/MD, #Jarvis Brown on Keys & #Will Montgomery II on drums. 
These will be jazz sets..
•
Next up, 2 Shows/1 Night [Sun 11.12] at the very lovely Blue Jay Listening Room in Jacksonville, Fl @bluejayjax! I’m traveling with the same band which is another first for me so again, I’m thrilled to have these amazing musicians with me over several shows! This will be a jazz set.
•
Next up, 4 Shows /2 nights [Fri 11.17 & 
Sat 11.18] at one of my most favorite places to play anywhere, The Velvet Note in Alpharetta, Ga! My last shows here pre-pandemic, were magical & I can’t wait to get back! And I have a surprise special guest & it’s gonna be a party! Same band. These shows will be soul sets.
•
Next up, 2 Shows/1 Night [Thurs 11.30] I’ll be performing as the special guest of brilliant guitarist JJ Sansaverino as part of the Gerald Veasley Unscripted Series at South Jazz Kitchen. I’ve been wanting to play here forever and am incredibly honored to share the stage with one of my most favorite musicians. If you’ve never seen JJ before, he is a consummate musician & mesmerizing performer. This ain’t gonna be nothing but a GOOD TIME!!
•
Next up, 1 Show/1 Night [Tues 12.05] I’ll be the special guest of JJ Sansaverino for a second time, for JJ’s Annual Holiday Show, along with 2 members of DW3 at the Iridium in NYC. It’s gonna  be fun & festive and fill you with all the Christmas vibes!
•
I CAN NOT WAIT TO SEE YOU!! 
See you all very soon!
Ticket links in bio❤️

Get ready to jingle all the way into the holiday season with the most enchanting Christmas show of the year! My homeboy and sensational jazz guitarist JJ Sansaverino, is teaming up with the dynamic harmonies of D3 and myself, Vivian Sessoms for a night of unforgettable music and festive cheer at the iconic Iridium in New York City.

Step into a winter wonderland as JJ sets the stage aglow with his virtuosic guitar skills, effortlessly blending his original compositions and unique arrangements of beloved Christmas classics.

Together, these extraordinary artists, along with Etienne Lytle (Keys), Al Carty (Bass), and Eric Brown (Drums) will take you on a musical sleigh ride, but don’t be surprised if they throw in some unexpected surprises, infusing their own unique twists and improvisations to keep you on your toes.

So, grab your loved ones and wrap yourself in the warmth of the holiday spirit as JJ Sansaverino, Vivian Sessoms, and the members of DW3 bring their sensational talents to the Iridium stage. With their magical blend of music, this Christmas show promises to be an unforgettable celebration of love, joy, and the true essence of the holiday season. 

Don’t miss out on this enchanting evening of musical brilliance – book your tickets now and be prepared to have your heartstrings strummed and your spirits lifted!
